description: Conventional Commits policy for pull request titles
globs: ["**/*"]
alwaysApply: true
---

- Pull Request titles must follow the Conventional Commits specification (e.g., `feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `refactor:`, `chore:`, `test:`, `perf:`, `build:`, `ci:`, `revert:`)
- Use scope when helpful (e.g., `feat(cli_types): ...`)

